# Authentication & Authorization

All authentication is handled by **Clerk**. Never implement custom auth logic.

## Getting the Current User

Use Clerk's server-side helpers to get the authenticated user:

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
```

## Data Access Rules

**Users must only access their own data.** Always scope database queries to the authenticated `userId`.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — no user scoping
const decks = await db.select().from(flashcardDecks);

// ✅ GOOD — scoped to current user
const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

const decks = await db
  .select()
  .from(flashcardDecks)
  .where(eq(flashcardDecks.userId, userId));
```

## Key Rules

- Always check `userId` before any DB read or write
- Every table that holds user data must have a `userId` column
- Never expose another user's data — even by accident via a shared ID in the URL
- Validate ownership before updates/deletes (re-query with `userId` filter, don't trust client-supplied IDs alone)
